               <msContents>
                  <summary>An incomplete copy of the romance of <title>Farhād va Shīrīn</title> by
                     Vaḥshī Bāfqī (d. 1583), which ends at the 23rd of 44 parts. It formerly
                     belonged to <persName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/102326800/"
                        key="person_102326800">Sir William Jones (1746–1794)</persName>, who made
                     many notes therein. It appears that he probably commissioned his friend
                        <persName role="scr" key="person_f7930">Bahman, son of Bahman, son of
                        Isfandiyar, d. 1788</persName>it during his tenure in Calcutta. </summary>

                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_187-item1">
                     <author key="person_30738316" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/30738316/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Vaḥshī Bāfqī, d.
                           1583</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">وحشى بافقى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <editor role="pat" key="person_102326800" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/102326800/"
                           ><persName>Jones, William, Sir, 1746–1794</persName></editor>
                     <editor role="scr" key="person_f7930"><persName>Bahman, son of Bahman, son of
                           Isfandiyar, d. 1788</persName></editor>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20320" change="#ids-cleanup">Farhād va
                        Shīrīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" key="work_20320"
                        change="#ids-cleanup">Shīrīn va Farhād</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_20320" change="#ids-cleanup">فرهاد
                        وشيرين</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" type="alt" key="work_20320" change="#ids-cleanup">شيرين و
                        فرهاد</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa" type="basmala"><locus from="1b" to="1b"> برگ ۱پ (folio
                           1b):</locus> الهی سینه‌ٔ ده آتش افروز * در آن سینه دلی وآندل همه
                        سوز</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">
                        <locus from="66a" to="66a"> برگ ۶۶ر (folio 66a):</locus> اگر چه صد نوا بیرون
                        دهد چنگ * چو نیکو بنگری باشد یک آهنگ </explicit>
                     <colophon xml:lang="fa">
                        <locus from="66a" to="66a"> برگ ۶۶ر (folio 66a):</locus> تمت نسخه شیرینن و
                        فرهاد تصنیف وحشی </colophon>
                     <colophon>Uninformative colophon.</colophon>
                     <note>While J. Lawrence suggests that Jones' associated ʿIzz al-Dīn completed this volume, it appears to very closely comport with <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6612"><idno>Persian
                              MS 133</idno></ref> completed by  by <persName>Bahman, son of Bahman, son of Isfandiyar,
                                 d. 1788</persName> for Jones before his death. For other volumes that
                        Jones owned now held in the Rylands, see <ref
                           target="https://www.digitalcollections.manchester.ac.uk/view/MS-PERSIAN-00010/"
                              ><idno>Persian MS 10</idno></ref>, <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6673">192</ref>,
                           <ref
                           target="https://www.digitalcollections.manchester.ac.uk/view/MS-PERSIAN-000219"
                           >219</ref>, <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6725">240</ref>,
                           <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6754"
                           >267</ref>, and <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6836">340</ref>.</note>

                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
